commit f992d6e04ce581b8e36836776fe721ad1d7193ec
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 18:05:05 2026 -0400

    feat(forms)(submissions): wire persist-then-notify into the form action skeleton; migrate contact/volunteer/registration

    Branch 7.3. Insert Submissions.persist between decode and notify in the
    generic formAction skeleton: a valid submission is written to its durable
    submissions/<form>/<id>.json object FIRST, and notify then runs over the
    stored Submission (the email references the persisted record). persist
    returning before notify makes a notify failure provably unable to lose the
    record (settled #8).

    - runtime: wire Submissions.layer/Service into AppServices + AppRuntime;
      extract makeAppLayer(storageLayer) + makeRequestRuntimeFromLayer so a test
      exercises the persist write end-to-end over an in-memory bucket.
    - action.ts: persist-then-notify; notify now receives the stored Submission.
    - contact/volunteer: notify reads submission.payload (was the bare decoded
      form); pipeline otherwise unchanged.
    - registration (net-new server persist): registration-action.ts decodes the
      { registrants: [...] } shell against Schema.Array(definitionToSchema(def)),
      persists each registrant as its own Submission, then notifies; the three
      {2024,2025,2026}/form routes drop their no-op actions and share one
      configured registration-route action; routes pass actionData?.result.
    - translations: registration.form.error/success.{title,description} EN+FR.
    - action.test.ts: persist-then-notify wiring incl. a persist-first proof (a
      notify failure still leaves the record on the in-memory bucket).

