 71	 * runs the form-specific notification over the PERSISTED `Submission` (the durable
 72	 * record, already on the bucket — so the email can reference its id) and fails
 73	 * (with any `AppError`, e.g. a mailer failure mapped to a form-level key) to abort
 74	 * the redirect; `success` is the post-submit toast copy.
 75	 *
 76	 * `notify` receives the stored `Submission`, not the bare decoded payload: by the
 77	 * time it runs, `Submissions.persist` has already written
 78	 * `submissions/<form>/<id>.json`, so the record survives a notify failure
 79	 * (settled #8). `notify`'s context is the form-notification slice of the request
 80	 * runtime (`makeRequestRuntime`): `Mailer` (every form notifies by mail today),
 81	 * plus `ReactRouterContext` / `Content` for a notifier that needs the request or
 82	 * page/form copy.
