 98	 * `routeFormAction` (the same wrapper the hand-tuned forms use), so a migrated
 99	 * route is `export const action = formAction({ form, notify, success })` — no
100	 * inline pipeline. The body yields a {@link FormSuccess} only to satisfy the
101	 * wrapper's body type; on the happy path the terminal `toast.redirect` fails with
102	 * a `RedirectError` the wrapper forwards to the runtime, so the return is
103	 * unreachable on success.
104	 *
105	 * Pipeline:
106	 *   1. `Content.getForm(form)` → the form's `FormDefinition`;
107	 *   2. `decodeForm(definition, submission.payload)` → on failure,
108	 *      `formValidationError(formatSchemaResult(...))` (bucketed field/form errors);
109	 *   3. `Submissions.persist(form, decoded)` → the durable record is written to
110	 *      `submissions/<form>/<id>.json` and returned BEFORE any notification;
111	 *   4. `notify(submission)` — the caller's form-specific notification OF the
